According to its documentation, `__len__` and `__getitem__` are sufficient. My type hinter complains about the implementation of `__getitem__` though, although my implementation follows the [python docs](https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__getitem__).

My current version is the following (with warnings from basedpyright):
```python
from collections.abc import Sequence
from typing import override

class MySeq(Sequence[float]):
    def __init__(self):
        self._data: list[float] = list()

    @override
    def __len__(self) -&gt; int:
