  [2]: https://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/20/orm/session_api.html#sqlalchemy.orm.Session.info
  [3]: https://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/20/orm/session_events.html#basic-query-interception

If the constants have meaning that only makes sense in relation to the class, then I prefer keeping them defined on the class with a inner class definition.

     
    class A:
        class Constants:
            CT_A = 1.0
            CT_B = 2.0
            
        def __init__(self):
            ...
            
        def method_class(self):
