Failing to include it might work for a while, but almost certainly will come back and bite in the ass at a later time, and it will do it so hard that someone (unfortunately, often not the same person who wrote the faulty code) will spend much more time (than writing it in the 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; place) fixing subtle errors (or crashes).

